# Convert 'Churn' variable from "Yes"/"No" to numeric (1/0)
churn$Churn <- ifelse(churn$Churn == "Yes", 1, 0)

# Drop 'customerID' — it's just an identifier and adds no predictive value
churn <- churn %>% select(-customerID)

# Handle nested variables
# 'PhoneService' and 'MultipleLines' are related — only keep one to avoid multicollinearity
churn <- churn %>% select(-MultipleLines)

#Do an 80/20 split of the data
set.seed(1) # for reproducibility
train = sample(1:nrow(churn), 0.8*nrow(churn))
test = -train
x = model.matrix(Churn~., data = churn) 
y = churn$Churn

ridge.cv     <- cv.glmnet(x[train,], y[train], family = "binomial", alpha = 0)
ridge.lambda <- ridge.cv$lambda.min
cat("Ridge optimal λ:", round(ridge.lambda,4), "\n")
## Ridge optimal λ: 0.0155
# Predict probabilities on test set
ridge.pred <- predict(
  ridge.cv, 
  s    = "lambda.min", 
  newx = x[test,], 
  type = "response"
)[,1]

# ROC & AUC
ridge.roc <- roc(y[test], ridge.pred)
## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1
## Setting direction: controls < cases
plot(ridge.roc, main = "ROC Curve — Ridge") 

cat("Ridge AUC:", round(auc(ridge.roc),4), "\n")
## Ridge AUC: 0.8504
#Give accuracy, sensitivity, and specificity
predicted_classes <- ifelse(ridge.pred > 0.5, 1, 0)
confusion_matrix <- table(y[test], predicted_classes)
confusion_matrix
##    predicted_classes
##       0   1
##   0 937  88
##   1 165 217
accuracy <- sum(diag(confusion_matrix)) / sum(confusion_matrix)
accuracy
## [1] 0.8201848

(d) Fit a glm with lasso to training data and evaluate the roc and auc of this model on testing data.

lasso.cv     <- cv.glmnet(x[train,], y[train], family = "binomial", alpha = 1)
lasso.lambda <- lasso.cv$lambda.min
cat("Lasso optimal λ:", round(lasso.lambda,4), "\n")
## Lasso optimal λ: 4e-04
lasso.pred <- predict(
  lasso.cv, 
  s    = "lambda.min", 
  newx = x[test,], 
  type = "response"
)[,1]

# ROC & AUC
lasso.roc <- roc(y[test], lasso.pred)
## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1
## Setting direction: controls < cases
plot(lasso.roc, main = "ROC Curve — Lasso") 

cat("Lasso AUC:", round(auc(lasso.roc),4), "\n")
## Lasso AUC: 0.8545

#Create a DNN model
model <- keras_model_sequential() %>%
  layer_dense(units = 64, activation = 'relu', input_shape = ncol(x[train,])) %>%
  layer_dropout(rate = 0.5) %>%
  layer_dense(units = 32, activation = 'relu') %>%
  layer_dropout(rate = 0.5) %>%
  layer_dense(units = 1, activation = 'sigmoid')
summary(model)
## Model: "sequential"
## ________________________________________________________________________________
##  Layer (type)                       Output Shape                    Param #     
## ================================================================================
##  dense_2 (Dense)                    (None, 64)                      1920        
##  dropout_1 (Dropout)                (None, 64)                      0           
##  dense_1 (Dense)                    (None, 32)                      2080        
##  dropout (Dropout)                  (None, 32)                      0           
##  dense (Dense)                      (None, 1)                       33          
## ================================================================================
## Total params: 4,033
## Trainable params: 4,033
## Non-trainable params: 0
## ________________________________________________________________________________
# Compile the model
model %>% compile(
  loss = 'binary_crossentropy',
  optimizer = optimizer_rmsprop(),
  metrics = c('accuracy')
)
# Fit the model
history <- model %>% fit(
  x[train,], y[train],
  epochs = 50,
  batch_size = 32,
  validation_split = 0.2
)
